createTemplate(address,bytes32,bytes).details: A specific set of request parameters will always have the same template ID. This means a few things: (1) You can compute the expected ID of a template before creating it, (2) Creating a new template with the same parameters will overwrite the old one and return the same ID, (3) After you query a template with its ID, you can verify its integrity by applying the hash and comparing the result with the ID.

params.parameters: Static request parameters (i.e., parameters that will not change between requests, unlike the dynamic parameters determined at request-time)

getTemplates(bytes32[]).details: Does not revert if the templates being indexed do not exist
